{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"f89ac754-d98e-4aa7-8c6c-2ed093e9a1c3","content":"There's no workflow file in the current directory, so here's general guidance for the switch:\n\n### 1. NuGet.org Setup\n- Go to **NuGet.org → Manage Packages → [your package] → Trusted publishers**\n- Add a GitHub Actions policy specifying your **repo**, **branch/tag pattern**, and optionally the **workflow filename**\n\n### 2. Workflow Changes\n\n**Add `id-token` permission** (required for OIDC):\n```yaml\npermissions:\n  id-token: write   # request OIDC token\n  contents: read\n```\n\n**Replace your `dotnet nuget push` step:**\n\n```yaml\n# BEFORE\n- run: dotnet nuget push **/*.nupkg --api-key ${{ secrets.NUGET_API_KEY }} --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n\n# AFTER\n- run: dotnet nuget push **/*.nupkg --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n```\n\nNo `--api-key` flag — the CLI automatically uses the OIDC token when trusted publishing is configured.\n\n### 3. Clean Up\n- Remove `secrets.NUGET_API_KEY` from your repo's **Settings → Secrets** once verified.\n\n### Key Points\n- The OIDC token is **short-lived** and scoped to the workflow run — no long-lived secrets to rotate.\n- Requires `dotnet` SDK **8.0.400+** or the `nuget` CLI **6.12+**.\n- If your workflow runs on `pull_request`, the `id-token` permission won't be available for forked PRs (by design).\n\nWant me to modify a specific workflow file?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"2d50e187-f3f3-48b2-afe2-4d82cbbe11ea","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"There are no files in the repository. The user is asking a general question about switching from NuGet API key to OIDC trusted publishing. Let me provide guidance based on my knowledge.","outputTokens":461,"requestId":"0407:32BB22:469AEC:526383:69F0050A"},"id":"ea654fa0-1cf4-4bf7-bfef-1ce27db5ee46","timestamp":"2026-04-28T00:53:42.651Z","parentId":"2b1c300e-c939-4ef2-9c7a-cc4de5c814ae"}
